<%= render "shared/breadcrumbs", items: [
  { name: "Home", url: root_path },
  { name: "About" }
] %>

<article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-4xl mx-auto">
  <h1>About CalcWise</h1>

  <p>CalcWise is a free online calculator platform offering <strong>74+ calculators</strong> across six categories. Our mission is to make quick, accurate calculations accessible to everyone — no sign-ups, no fees, no data collection.</p>

  <h2>What We Offer</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><%= link_to "Finance Calculators", category_path("finance") %>:</strong> Mortgage, loan, compound interest, investment, retirement, tax brackets, credit card payoff, auto loan, home affordability, net worth, business loan, currency converter, and more.</li>
    <li><strong><%= link_to "Math Calculators", category_path("math") %>:</strong> Percentage, fraction, area, circle, exponent, Pythagorean theorem, quadratic equation, standard deviation, GCD/LCM, sample size, and aspect ratio.</li>
    <li><strong><%= link_to "Physics Calculators", category_path("physics") %>:</strong> Velocity, force, kinetic energy, Ohm's law, projectile motion, element mass/volume, unit converter, electricity cost, wire gauge, decibel, wavelength, and planet weight.</li>
    <li><strong><%= link_to "Health Calculators", category_path("health") %>:</strong> BMI, calorie, body fat, TDEE, macros, pace, pregnancy due date, pregnancy week tracker, water intake, sleep cycles, one rep max, dog age, and dog food.</li>
    <li><strong><%= link_to "Construction Calculators", category_path("construction") %>:</strong> Paint, flooring, concrete, gravel/mulch, and fence material estimators.</li>
    <li><strong><%= link_to "Everyday Calculators", category_path("everyday") %>:</strong> Tip, discount, age, date difference, gas mileage, fuel cost, GPA, and cooking converter.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How Our Calculators Work</h2>
  <p>Every calculator on CalcWise is built with a focus on accuracy and usability:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Instant results</strong> — calculations happen in real-time as you type. No "Calculate" button needed.</li>
    <li><strong>Educational content</strong> — every calculator page includes the formulas used, step-by-step explanations, and frequently asked questions.</li>
    <li><strong>Privacy by design</strong> — all calculations happen locally in your browser. We never see, store, or transmit the numbers you enter.</li>
    <li><strong>Mobile-friendly</strong> — optimized for phones, tablets, and desktops.</li>
    <li><strong>No registration</strong> — just visit and calculate. No account needed.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our Blog</h2>
  <p>The <%= link_to "CalcWise Blog", blog_path %> features in-depth articles on topics related to our calculators — from personal finance guides to health and fitness tips. Our articles are written to help you understand the concepts behind the calculations and make more informed decisions.</p>

  <h2>Accuracy and Methodology</h2>
  <p>Our calculators use industry-standard formulas and methodologies:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Financial calculators use standard amortization formulas and current (2024) tax bracket data</li>
    <li>Health calculators use peer-reviewed equations (Mifflin-St Jeor for BMR, Navy method for body fat, etc.)</li>
    <li>Physics calculators use standard SI-unit equations from established textbooks</li>
  </ul>
  <p>While we strive for accuracy, our calculators provide <strong>estimates for informational purposes</strong>. Please see our <%= link_to "Disclaimer", disclaimer_path %> for important limitations.</p>

  <h2>How CalcWise Is Supported</h2>
  <p>CalcWise is a free service supported by advertising through Google AdSense. Ad revenue allows us to keep all calculators free and continue developing new tools. We are committed to maintaining a clean, user-friendly experience and will never let advertising interfere with the functionality of our calculators.</p>

  <h2>Contact Us</h2>
  <p>Have a question, found a bug, or want to suggest a new calculator? We'd love to hear from you. Visit our <%= link_to "Contact page", contact_path %> to get in touch.</p>
</article>
